This paper deals with action localization in videos, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves self-attention and transformer encoders, which are techniques commonly used in natural language processing (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of a new dataset, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR) or multimedia (cs.MM).
